article.headline: Fresno State 89, Norfolk State 70
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Ja'Vance Coleman scored 25 points and Quinton Hosley added 23 as Fresno State bounced back from consecutive losses to beat Norfolk State 89-70 on Monday night. The Bulldogs (5-3) used a full-court man defense to rattle Norfolk State, coming up with 14 steals and forcing 23 turnovers. Hosley had four of the steals and 11 rebounds. Tony Murphy scored 24 points to lead Norfolk State. The Spartans stayed close for a while by dominating the boards to get second chances. They outrebounded Fresno State 49-33 and had 20 offensive rebounds. Norfolk State cut the lead to 54-46 with 14:21 in the second half when Tony Murphy drove in for a layup, but the Bulldogs pulled away. Coleman scored 15 points in the second half. He made four 3-pointers and added five assists. Teammate Kevin Bell finished with eight assists and six points, while turning the ball over only once. The Bulldogs built a 38-31 halftime lead despite missing 14 of their first 19 shots. Both teams, however, shot poorly with Fresno State at 35.9 percent and Norfolk State at 36.1 percent at the break.
